In JIRA 5.0, there is a new permission called 'Browse Users'. If the Project Administrator does not have this Browse Users permission, they can't search for user when trying to add user to Project Role membership. They will need to fill in the username directly to the field. According to the [documentation|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Managing+Project+Role+Membership#ManagingProjectRoleMembership-Assigningausertoaprojectrole]:
{quote}
# Open the People page (see Screenshot 2) as described in 'Viewing project role members' above.
# Hover over the Users column for the project role in which you are interested (e.g. Administrators) and click the yellow box which appears.
# The users and groups will become editable (see Screenshot 3). Type the name of the user(s) you wish to add to this project role. Then click the Update button.
{quote}

Actually, the Project Administrator (without Browse Users permission) need to type in the username and press 'Enter' before clicking the 'Update' button or it will not work.

The documentation need to be updated so that the Project Administrator (without Browse Users permission) know how to add the user to the Project Role.

