When accessing a sub-task with SOAP that has Issue Security set, if the user does not have access to the task they cannot view the issue. The following error is generated: com.atlassian.jira.rpc.exception.RemotePermissionException: This issue does not exist or you don't have permission to view it.

h5. To recreate:

# Create an Issue Security scheme, such as as Reporter, Assignee and Project Lead.
# Create a task and set that Issue Security.
# Create a sub-task.
# Assign the sub-task to a user who is not the Reporter or Project Lead.
(i) They will be able to view the sub-task, but not the task, for example:
!sub_task.jpg!
# Attempt to retrieve the issue through SOAP. Example perl script below.

{code:title=Soap Script}
#!/usr/bin/perl
# jira perl client using SOAP logs in, 
# handles failure or prints issue fields,
# then logs out.

use strict;
use warnings;
use SOAP::Lite;
use Data::Dumper;

my $soap = SOAP::Lite->proxy('http://localhost/rpc/soap/jirasoapservice-v2?wsdl');
my $auth = $soap->login("testdeveloper", "sphere")->result();
my $call = $soap->getIssue($auth,'SOAP-4');

if ($call->fault()) {
    print $call->faultdetail;
    print "\n";
    print $call->faultstring;
    die;
} else {
    print "Getting example issue, hang tight\n";
    print Dumper($call->result);
}
$soap->logout($auth)
{code}

This will generate the error.

